The paper deals with online algorithms, which are commonly studied in computer science theory and optimization. The mention of the Metrical Task System (MTS) suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the discussion of competitive ratio and regret minimization points towards game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of an existing regret minimization algorithm and the mention of an expert algorithm suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
